---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import ReferencePageShell from "../../components/ReferencePageShell.astro";

---

<Layout title="Knitting Machine Brand Names Worldwide">

<ReferencePageShell
  title="Knitting Machine Brand Names Worldwide"
  subhead="Many knitting machines were sold under different brand names around the world. This chart helps identify equivalent machines across Brother, Silver Reed, Studio, KnitKing, Elna, and other brands."
  backHref="/learn/reference#category-machine-reference"
  backLabel="Back to Machine References"
>
    <figure class="machine-brand-chart">
      <img
        src="/images/references/Knitting-machine-brands-worldwide.jpg"
        alt="Knitting machine brand names worldwide comparison chart"
      />

      <figcaption>
        Knitting machines were frequently sold under different brand names depending
        on the country where they were distributed.
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <section class="reference-notes">

      <h2>Why machines have different brand names</h2>

      <p>
        During the peak years of home knitting machines, manufacturers often partnered
        with distributors in different countries. The same machine might appear under
        several different brand names even though the underlying design and parts were
        identical.
      </p>

      <p>
        Understanding these relationships can make it easier to find manuals,
        accessories, replacement parts, and tutorials for your machine.
      </p>

    </section>

</ReferencePageShell>

</Layout>

<style>

.machine-brand-chart {
  margin: 40px auto;
  text-align: center;
}

.machine-brand-chart img {
  max-width: 100%;
  height: auto;
  border-radius: 8px;
}

.machine-brand-chart figcaption {
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  margin-top: 10px;
  color: #666;
}

.reference-notes {
  max-width: 800px;
  margin: 40px auto;
}

</style>